   "source": [
    "# SAX, StAX & DOM \u2014 Practice Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook focuses primarily on **SAX, StAX, and DOM** \u2014 the three Java\n",
    "techniques for reading and writing XML. The fundamentals of what XML is and\n",
    "how it's structured are more the domain of Text Technology, so they're not\n",
    "covered here.\n",
    "\n",
    "You'll work through a short conceptual warm-up, then write small pieces of\n",
    "real SAX, StAX, and DOM code against the same example document, and finish\n",
    "with a few \"which technology would you pick?\" scenarios.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Estimated time: ~60\u201370 minutes.**\n",
    "\n",
    "All exercises use the same XML string, a small address book:\n",
    "\n",
    "```xml\n",
    "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n",
    "<addressbook>\n",
    "    <address>\n",
    "        <forename>Camellya</forename>\n",
    "        <surname/>\n",
    "        <email>crazy@blackshores.com</email>\n",
    "        <powerlevel>340</powerlevel>\n",
    "    </address>\n",
    "    <address>\n",
    "        <forename>Cantarella</forename>\n",
    "        <surname>Fisalia</surname>\n",
    "        <email></email>\n",
    "        <powerlevel>875</powerlevel>\n",
    "    </address>\n",
    "    <address>\n",
    "        <forename>Ciaccona</forename>\n",
    "        <surname></surname>\n",
    "        <email>kawaii-bard@wuwa.com</email>\n",
    "        <powerlevel>120</powerlevel>\n",
    "    </address>\n",
    "    <address>\n",
    "        <forename>Carlotta</forename>\n",
    "        <surname>Montelli</surname>\n",
    "        <email>opal@rinascita.com</email>\n",
    "        <powerlevel>610</powerlevel>\n",
    "    </address>\n",
    "</addressbook>\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Notice that `surname` and `email` aren't always filled in for every entry \u2014\n",
    "that's intentional. Empty and self-closing elements behave slightly\n",
    "differently depending on which API you're using, and the exercises below\n",
    "will have you run into that directly rather than just being told about it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the cell below first \u2014 every later section reuses the `addressBookXml`\n",
    "variable it defines."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "d89c8151",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
