    "## Part 2 \u2014 SAX\n",
    "\n",
    "SAX pushes events at a `DefaultHandler` you write. Below is a handler that\n",
    "should count the `<address>` elements in the address book and sum up every\n",
    "`<powerlevel>` value. Unlike a value stored in an *attribute*, a\n",
    "`<powerlevel>` value is *element text content* \u2014 so you can't just read it\n",
    "off in `startElement` the way you'd read an attribute. You need to track\n",
    "\"am I currently inside a `<powerlevel>` element?\" and pick the text up in\n",
    "`characters()`, then react again in `endElement()`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Fill in the four `// TODO` lines."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "1f1e6cd1",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler;\n",
    "import org.xml.sax.Attributes;\n",
    "import org.xml.sax.SAXException;\n",
    "\n",
    "class AddressBookSaxHandler extends DefaultHandler {\n",
    "    int addressCount = 0;\n",
    "    int totalPower = 0;\n",
    "    boolean insidePowerlevel = false;\n",
    "\n",
    "    @Override\n",
    "    public void startElement(String uri, String localName, String qName, Attributes attrs)\n",
    "            throws SAXException {\n",
    "        if (qName.equals(\"address\")) {\n",
    "            // TODO: increment addressCount by 1\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        if (qName.equals(\"powerlevel\")) {\n",
    "            // TODO: set insidePowerlevel to true\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    @Override\n",
    "    public void characters(char[] ch, int start, int length) throws SAXException {\n",
    "        if (insidePowerlevel) {\n",
    "            String text = new String(ch, start, length).trim();\n",
    "            if (!text.isEmpty()) {\n",
    "                // TODO: parse text as an int and add it to totalPower\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    @Override\n",
    "    public void endElement(String uri, String localName, String qName) throws SAXException {\n",
    "        if (qName.equals(\"powerlevel\")) {\n",
    "            // TODO: set insidePowerlevel back to false\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "System.out.println(\"AddressBookSaxHandler defined.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92f99f06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now run the parser. This part is already complete \u2014 just run it and\n",
    "see what your handler produced."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "a9e4d132",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import javax.xml.parsers.SAXParserFactory;\n",
    "import javax.xml.parsers.SAXParser;\n",
    "import org.xml.sax.InputSource;\n",
    "import java.io.StringReader;\n",
    "\n",
    "AddressBookSaxHandler saxHandler = new AddressBookSaxHandler();\n",
    "SAXParser saxParser = SAXParserFactory.newInstance().newSAXParser();\n",
    "saxParser.parse(new InputSource(new StringReader(addressBookXml)), saxHandler);\n",
    "\n",
    "System.out.println(\"Addresses found: \" + saxHandler.addressCount);\n",
    "System.out.println(\"Total power level: \" + saxHandler.totalPower);"
   ]
  },
