   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f722d815",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3 \u2014 StAX\n",
    "\n",
    "StAX is also a serial, event-based reader, but *your* code pulls events\n",
    "with `hasNext()` / `nextEvent()` instead of waiting for callbacks. Below,\n",
    "fill in the three `// TODO` lines so the loop collects every `<forename>`\n",
    "text into the `forenames` list.\n",
    "\n",
    "Reminder from the slides: cast with `event.asStartElement()` /\n",
    "`event.asCharacters()` / `event.asEndElement()` only after checking\n",
    "`isStartElement()` / `isCharacters()` / `isEndElement()`, to avoid a\n",
    "`ClassCastException`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "fb8c8a52",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import javax.xml.stream.XMLInputFactory;\n",
    "import javax.xml.stream.XMLEventReader;\n",
    "import javax.xml.stream.events.XMLEvent;\n",
    "import javax.xml.stream.events.StartElement;\n",
    "import javax.xml.stream.events.Characters;\n",
    "import java.io.StringReader;\n",
    "import java.util.ArrayList;\n",
    "import java.util.List;\n",
    "\n",
    "XMLInputFactory staxInputFactory = XMLInputFactory.newInstance();\n",
    "XMLEventReader staxReader = staxInputFactory.createXMLEventReader(new StringReader(addressBookXml));\n",
    "\n",
    "List<String> forenames = new ArrayList<>();\n",
    "boolean insideForename = false;\n",
    "\n",
    "while (staxReader.hasNext()) {\n",
    "    XMLEvent event = staxReader.nextEvent();\n",
    "\n",
    "    if (event.isStartElement()) {\n",
    "        StartElement se = event.asStartElement();\n",
    "        if (se.getName().getLocalPart().equals(\"forename\")) {\n",
    "            // TODO: set insideForename to true\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    if (event.isCharacters() && insideForename) {\n",
    "        Characters chars = event.asCharacters();\n",
    "        // TODO: add the trimmed text (chars.getData()) to the forenames list\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    if (event.isEndElement()) {\n",
    "        // TODO: if this end tag's local name is \"forename\", set insideForename back to false\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "System.out.println(forenames);"
   ]
  },
  {
