  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1f7b9a17",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 4 \u2014 DOM\n",
    "\n",
    "DOM is different from the other two: it parses the whole document into an\n",
    "in-memory tree first, *then* you navigate it however you like \u2014 including\n",
    "modifying it, which SAX and StAX cannot do.\n",
    "\n",
    "**4a.** Parse `addressBookXml` into a `Document`, then collect every\n",
    "`<email>` element's text content into the `emails` list. Fill in the one\n",
    "`// TODO`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Look closely at what you get back for Cantarella's `<email></email>` once\n",
    "you run it \u2014 an empty element's `getTextContent()` is not `null`, it's an\n",
    "empty string `\"\"`. That matters: code that assumed `null` and guarded with\n",
    "a null-check would let an empty string slip through and could blow up\n",
    "elsewhere (e.g. an unguarded `.length()` call downstream), while code that\n",
    "assumes there's always *some* text would just silently produce a blank\n",
    "entry instead of flagging that the field was never filled in."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "69353d68",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory;\n",
    "import javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder;\n",
    "import org.w3c.dom.Document;\n",
    "import org.w3c.dom.NodeList;\n",
    "import org.xml.sax.InputSource;\n",
    "import java.io.StringReader;\n",
    "import java.util.ArrayList;\n",
    "import java.util.List;\n",
    "\n",
    "DocumentBuilderFactory domFactory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();\n",
    "DocumentBuilder domBuilder = domFactory.newDocumentBuilder();\n",
    "Document addressBookDoc = domBuilder.parse(new InputSource(new StringReader(addressBookXml)));\n",
    "\n",
    "NodeList emailNodes = addressBookDoc.getElementsByTagName(\"email\");\n",
    "List<String> emails = new ArrayList<>();\n",
    "\n",
    "for (int i = 0; i < emailNodes.getLength(); i++) {\n",
    "    // TODO: get the trimmed text content of emailNodes.item(i)\n",
    "    //       and add it to the emails list\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "System.out.println(emails);"
   ]
  },
  {
